HEADWORD: Genealogy
<hw>Gen`e*al"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Genealogies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE.
<ets>genealogi</ets>, <ets>genelogie</ets>, OF. <ets>genelogie</ets>, F.
<ets>g⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧alogie</ets>, L. <ets>genealogia</ets>, fr. Gr.
<?/; <?/ birth, race, descent (akin to L. <ets>genus</ets>) + <?/
discourse.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An account or history of the descent of a person or
family from an ancestor; enumeration of ancestors and their children in
the natural order of succession; a pedigree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Regular descent of a person or family from a
progenitor; pedigree; lineage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

